{"id": 243357380, "title": "Five tank-bound Army soldiers swept away while crossing river in Ladakh", "text": "Five soldiers of the Army are feared drowned after they were swept away while crossing a river in a T-72 tank near the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in the Nyoma-Chushul area in Ladakh early Saturday, officials said.They said the incident occurred near Mandir Morh, 148 kilometres from here, during an exercise around 1 am.The T-72 tank with five soldiers on board sank due to flash floods while they were crossing the river, the officials said.A rescue operation has been launched. Further details are awaited.", "summary": "Five soldiers of the Army are feared drowned after they were swept away while crossing a river in a T-72 tank near the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in the Nyoma-Chushul area in Ladakh early Saturday, officials said.\nThey said the incident occurred near Mandir Morh, 148 kilometres from here, during an exercise around 1 am.\nThe T-72 tank with five soldiers on board sank due to flash floods while they were crossing the river, the officials said.\nA rescue operation has been launched. Further details are awaited.", "url": "https://www.business-standard.com/external-affairs-defence-security/news/five-army-soldiers-in-tanks-swept-away-while-crossing-river-in-ladakh-124062900188_1.html", "image": "https://bsmedia.business-standard.com/_media/bs/img/article/2023-04/14/full/1681479096-3426.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 06:02:03", "author": "Press Trust of India", "authors": ["Press Trust of India"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.633}